      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's a bit vague lol. i'm specifically looking at the data that suggests there's a correlation between higher benefit levels and people dropping out of the workforce. a lot of people argue this is the main driver for the recent shifts in labor supply. do you think the data supports that specific link, or is it more complicated than that?",
